PGMODAYS-SUBMISSION-ABSTRACTS


Submission abstracts PGMODAYS 2019

   Submissions on all aspects of optimization and operations research,
   theoretical or applied, and their interfaces with data sciences, are
   welcome. The leaders of PGMO projects are especially encouraged to
   propose presentations on the topics of their project.

   The topics of this conference include :

   ✓continuous optimization (convex and non-convex, non-smooth...)
   ✓optimization of large systems (decomposition-coordination methods,...)
   ✓combinatorial optimization, integer or mixed programming
   ✓optimization under uncertainty  (stochastic and robust optimization)
   ✓global optimization (relaxation, approximation,semi-algebraic
   programing, stochastic algorithms...)
   ✓optimal control
   ✓PDE aspects of optimization (shape optimization, optimal transport,
   ...)
   ✓game theory
   ✓interfaces of optimization and data sciences, including statistical
   learning
   ✓related fields : risk management, uncertainties analysis
   ✓specific industrial applications of optimization and operations
   research : energy management, transportation, telecom networks,...

   The parallel talks will be scheduled on the second of the PGMO days,
   Wed 4th. The first day, Tue 3rd, will be dedicated to plenary lectures
   given by :

   Karen Aardal, Delft Institute of Applied Mathematics, Delft University
   of Technology
   Antonio Bicchi, Istituto Italiano di Tecnologia and Università di Pisa
   Friedrich Eisenbrand, Swiss Federal Institute of Technology Lausanne
   Rémi Munos, Deepmind Paris
   Shai Shalev-Shwartz, Mobileye, an Intel company and Hebrew university
   of Jerusalem

   and to the ceremony of the PGMO Phd Prize.


     *  Invited or tutorial sessions

   Invited sessions on selected topics are welcome. An invited session
   consists of one or two blocks. One block consists of 3 talks, of 30
   minutes each. The speakers in a given invited session should be of
   sufficiently diverse origins.  A small number of tutorial sessions
   (1h30) on advanced topics may also be organized. Such sessions will be
   scheduled in parallel with ordinary or invited sessions. Should you
   wish to organize an invited or tutorial session, please contact as soon
   as possible the coordination team:
   pgmodays-coordination@fondation-hadamard.fr

   The speakers participating to an invited or tutorial session will have
   to submit an abstract, following the general procedure.

Important dates

   • Extended deadline (firm), september 30 midnight, abstract submission

   Abstracts of one page should be submitted via easychair : closed

   Please follow the template to prepare your abstract : template.PDF and
   template.Tex

   . Mid of October, notification of acceptance

   Registration will open in October (registration is free of charge but
   mandatory)


